00:04:40,605 --> 00:04:45,643
It true you keep pictures of victims next to 
your bed, when you're working on a case?

63
00:04:45,643 --> 00:04:47,007
Where'd you hear that?

64
00:04:47,007 --> 00:04:48,516
People talk.

65
00:04:48,516 --> 00:04:50,944
Just seems a little freaky.

66
00:04:51,386 --> 00:04:55,307
Easy to look at all the files and boxes,

67
00:04:55,307 --> 00:04:57,666
forget the lives behind them.

68
00:04:58,904 --> 00:05:00,596
Joseph Shaw, 38.

69
00:05:00,596 --> 00:05:03,935
He was killed right before he was set
to testify against Corey Lewis.

70
00:05:03,935 --> 00:05:06,426
Shotgun blast to the face,
through the door.

71
00:05:06,426 --> 00:05:08,754
So suspect number one is Corey,

72
00:05:08,754 --> 00:05:10,589
who didn't want Joseph
taking the stand?

73
00:05:10,589 --> 00:05:13,282
But Corey was in jail
when Joseph was killed.

74
00:05:13,282 --> 00:05:15,823
Cops figured he must've reached out,
gotten someone else to do it.

75
00:05:15,823 --> 00:05:17,909
Yeah, but the kid didn't
seem to have much reach.

76
00:05:17,909 --> 00:05:21,174
Was a loner who lived at a rehab center
called Robinson teen house.

77
00:05:21,174 --> 00:05:23,291
Place Joseph worked as a counselor.

78
00:05:23,291 --> 00:05:25,055
Know it from my narcotics days.

79
00:05:25,055 --> 00:05:28,026
Treats drug-addicted teens from 
all backgrounds. Has a great rep.

80
00:05:28,026 --> 00:05:31,171
Yeah, it was started by Jane and 
Ted Robinson, big Philly philanthropists.

81
00:05:31,171 --> 00:05:35,466
Neighbor who ID'ed the body told the cops
Robinson house was Joseph's life.

82
00:05:35,466 --> 00:05:38,428
So maybe the Robinsons can
tell us more about our victim.

83
00:05:38,428 --> 00:05:42,208
Let's find out what Corey knows
about this credit card being used.

84
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:46,330
Now here's a guy who wouldn't 
look so bad on a bedside table.

85
00:05:58,700 --> 00:06:04,257
We started this place after our son
Tom died of a meth overdose.

86
00:06:04,257 --> 00:06:07,083
Being here has helped us as much
as it's helped any of the kids,

87
00:06:07,083 --> 00:06:08,793
to tell you the truth.

88
00:06:08,793 --> 00:06:10,532
Did you know Joseph Shaw well?

89
00:06:10,532 --> 00:06:13,244
Sure, and the kids loved Joseph.

90
00:06:13,244 --> 00:06:17,136
Well, he sweated through rehab
with them every step of the way.

91
00:06:17,136 --> 00:06:19,606
He struggled with heroin himself, 
growing up.

92
00:06:19,606 --> 00:06:22,620
He even did a few months in jail
before he got clean.

93
00:06:22,620 --> 00:06:24,686
So he knew what the kids
were going through.

94
00:06:24,686 --> 00:06:28,423
With a lot of social workers,
the kids are just a file.

95
00:06:28,423 --> 00:06:33,050
But Joseph always said it was important
to see the lives behind the file.

96
00:06:33,050 --> 00:06:35,089
And he did.

97
00:06:36,244 --> 00:06:41,326
Can you tell us about his relationship
with, uh, Corey, the boy accused of murder?

98
00:06:41,326 --> 00:06:44,183
Corey was like our son Tom,
in a lot of ways.

99
00:06:44,183 --> 00:06:47,998
He was tough, put up walls.

100
00:06:47,998 --> 00:06:50,961
But Joseph knew how to get through them,

101
00:06:50,961 --> 00:06:53,109
right from the start.

102
00:06:54,952 --> 00:06:57,401
Let me out of this damn prison!

103
00:06:57,401 --> 00:06:59,873
- The new guy's freaking out!
- Chill out, bro!

104
00:06:59,873 --> 00:07:02,274
Corey, we know what you're going through.

105
00:07:02,274 --> 00:07:05,525
You don't know anything.
You just met me yesterday, bitch!

106
00:07:05,525 --> 00:07:07,443
Let him slam.

107
00:07:07,443 --> 00:07:11,285
My son used to do this kind of thing all
the time, end up in hospitals.

108
00:07:11,285 --> 00:07:13,595
You're a strong bastard, aren't you?

109
00:07:13,595 --> 00:07:16,494
- I'm getting out of here, man.
- No, you're not.

110
00:07:16,494 --> 00:07:19,176
You know, when I was using, man,
I was hollowed-out and weak.

111
00:07:19,176 --> 00:07:20,908
What the hell are you talking about?

112
00:07:20,908 --> 00:07:23,494
You're in here because you're an addict, man. 
You got a disease.

113
00:07:23,494 --> 00:07:26,090
- That's bull, man!
- Denial. Been there, done that!

114
00:07:26,090 --> 00:07:29,500
What we do here Corey, is we try 
to help you kick addiction's ass.

115
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,728
It takes some serious muscle.

116
00:07:31,728 --> 00:07:35,129
There's a dent in that door tells me 
you're strong enough to pull it off.

117
00:07:35,129 --> 00:07:36,904
Bet I could put a dent in that door.

118
00:07:36,904 --> 00:07:38,981
I'd rather see you get to group, Orlando.

119
00:07:38,981 --> 00:07:42,989
You put that strength in the right direction,
you're gonna be a star here.

120
00:07:57,504 --> 00:08:00,116
We thought Corey was getting
on track after that.

121
00:08:00,116 --> 00:08:04,796
Was there anyone Corey was close to,
could have convinced to kill Joseph,

122
00:08:04,796 --> 00:08:07,164
- stop him from testifying?
- No.

123
00:08:07,164 --> 00:08:10,914
The other kids just didn't seem
to connect with Corey.

124
00:08:15,848 --> 00:08:18,597
Orlando and the witness
to his murder are dead,

125
00:08:18,597 --> 00:08:20,148
and you're free as a bird.

126
00:08:20,148 --> 00:08:22,024
Things worked out pretty good for you,
didn't they, Corey?

127
00:08:22,024 --> 00:08:24,364
Look, I don't have to talk about Orlando.

128
00:08:24,364 --> 00:08:25,973
Those charges were dropped.

129
00:08:25,973 --> 00:08:28,147
Fine. Let's talk about Joseph.

130
00:08:28,147 --> 00:08:29,770
I liked him.

131
00:08:29,770 --> 00:08:32,878
And I got an airtight alibi
for the night he was killed.

132
00:08:32,878 --> 00:08:36,271
Oh, someone just used his credit cards.
You got any ideas about that?

133
00:08:36,271 --> 00:08:39,373
No, but I'll tell you what I think.

134
00:08:39,373 --> 00:08:43,883
I think what sank Joseph is 
the same thing that always sinks a guy.

135
00:08:43,883 --> 00:08:45,828
Women.

136
00:08:45,828 --> 00:08:47,951
It's romantic of you, Corey.

137
00:08:47,951 --> 00:08:49,974
You know it's true.

138
00:08:50,538 --> 00:08:53,876
Come on, you've been sunk, too, right?

139
00:08:54,792 --> 00:08:56,894
Why don't you tell us what
the hell you're talking about?

140
00:08:56,894 --> 00:09:01,103
I'm talking about
how love makes people crazy.

141
00:09:04,781 --> 00:09:07,792
I couldn't keep my girlfriend,
'cause I was always lying,

142
00:09:07,792 --> 00:09:09,607
